      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MASTER KILCOY (1) had the drop on the lead and went on to be beaten 2.25 lengths into second (19.89) at this track in a TG1-4W over 342m. Has good early burn and is suited drawn on the inside. One of the contenders. BLACK WANDA (2) has some solid form under her belt and proved too strong last time to win by 1.5 lengths at this track in a handy 20.04 beating Tough Cookie. Good beginner aided by a nice draw. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. GETTING CHEEKY (5) stuck on well last time to finish half a length back in second (16.99) at Murray Bridge Straight in a Grade 6/MDN over 300m. Safe beginner but has a tricky box to overcome. Expected to be in this for a long way. KILCOY LASS (4) has a solid strike rate at this distance.",
